{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Corinthians 6 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:1",
      "text": "Working together with him, then, we entreat you not to accept the grace of God in vain.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:2",
      "text": "For he says, “At the acceptable time I have listened to you, and helped you on the day of salvation.” Behold, now is the acceptable time; behold, now is the day of salvation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:3",
      "text": "We put no obstacle in any one's way, so that no fault may be found with our ministry,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:4",
      "text": "but as servants of God we commend ourselves in every way: through great endurance, in afflictions, hardships, calamities,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:5",
      "text": "beatings, imprisonments, tumults, labors, watching, hunger;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:6",
      "text": "by purity, knowledge, forbearance, kindness, the Holy Spirit, genuine love,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:7",
      "text": "truthful speech, and the power of God; with the weapons of righteousness for the right hand and for the left;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:8",
      "text": "in honor and dishonor, in ill repute and good repute. We are treated as impostors, and yet are true;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:9",
      "text": "as unknown, and yet well known; as dying, and behold we live; as punished, and yet not killed;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:10",
      "text": "as sorrowful, yet always rejoicing; as poor, yet making many rich; as having nothing, and yet possessing everything.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:11",
      "text": "Our mouth is open to you, Corinthians; our heart is wide.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:12",
      "text": "You are not restricted by us, but you are restricted in your own affections.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:13",
      "text": "In return—I speak as to children—widen your hearts also.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:14",
      "text": "Do not be mismated with unbelievers. For what partnership have righteousness and iniquity? Or what fellowship has light with darkness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:15",
      "text": "What accord has Christ with Belial? Or what has a believer in common with an unbeliever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:16",
      "text": "What agreement has the temple of God with idols? For we are the temple of the living God; as God said, “I will live in them and move among them, and I will be their God, and they shall be my people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:17",
      "text": "Therefore come out from them, and be separate from them, says the Lord, and touch nothing unclean; then I will welcome you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-corinthians.6.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:18",
      "text": "and I will be a father to you, and you shall be my sons and daughters, says the Lord Almighty.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
